          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does keyword stuffing in GBP actually work?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>It can provide a short-term ranking boost because the GBP business name is a strong ranking signal. However, Google actively detects and removes keyword-stuffed names. Repeat violations lead to listing suspension, which eliminates all local visibility permanently — including your reviews.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What happens if I keyword stuff my Google Business Profile name?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google may silently edit your business name back to your legal name, suspend your listing temporarily, or permanently suspend it for repeated violations. Competitors can report the violation using "Suggest an edit" or the Business Redressal Complaint Form.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How can I rank in local search without stuffing my GBP name?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Use your accurate business name, then optimize GBP categories (primary and all applicable secondary categories), fill out services and products sections with keyword-rich descriptions, respond to reviews mentioning service keywords, and build consistent citations across directories.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can competitors report my GBP for keyword stuffing?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Any Google user can flag a listing as violating guidelines via "Suggest an edit" or through Google's Business Redressal Complaint Form. Local SEO professionals and competitors actively monitor and report keyword-stuffed names — especially in high-competition verticals like legal, medical, and home services.</p></div></div>
